    "exec-summary": {
      "id": "exec-summary",
      "name": "Executive Summary",
      "content": "<p><strong>The Opportunity</strong></p><p>The outlining and note-taking software market is fragmented between complex, feature-bloated tools (Notion, Obsidian) and simplistic apps that lack power. IdiamPro fills the gap: a professional-grade outliner that's fast, elegant, and works across platforms without requiring cloud storage or subscriptions.</p><p></p><p><strong>The Product</strong></p><p>IdiamPro is a cross-platform (macOS, iOS, Web) outlining application that prioritizes local-first data storage, keyboard-driven workflows, and a gesture model optimized for both desktop and mobile. Unlike competitors, we respect user privacy by default and never lock features behind arbitrary limitations.</p><p></p><p><strong>Target Market</strong></p><p>Primary: Knowledge workers, writers, researchers, students (TAM: ~50M users globally)</p><p>Secondary: Software developers, project managers, consultants</p><p></p><p><strong>Business Model</strong></p><p>Freemium with premium features. Free tier is generous (unlimited nodes, all features), paid tier removes outline limits and adds cloud sync. Pricing: $8/month or $80/year for individuals.</p><p></p><p><strong>Traction to Date</strong></p><p>\u2022 Product: 56+ features implemented, stable on 3 platforms</p><p>\u2022 Beta: Not yet launched</p><p>\u2022 Revenue: $0 (pre-launch)</p><p></p><p><strong>The Ask</strong></p><p>Bootstrap initially. Consider angel/seed funding ($100-300K) if traction validates aggressive growth opportunity. Exit strategy: sustainable lifestyle business or acquisition by larger player (Notion, Linear, Arc).</p>",
      "type": "chapter",
      "parentId": "root-planning",
      "childrenIds": [],
      "isCollapsed": false,
      "prefix": "1"
    },
    "market-analysis": {
      "id": "market-analysis",
      "name": "Market Analysis",
      "content": "<p>Deep dive into market landscape, competition, and positioning</p>",
      "type": "chapter",
      "parentId": "root-planning",
      "childrenIds": [
        "market-size",
        "competitors",
        "positioning",
        "user-personas"
      ],
      "isCollapsed": false,
      "prefix": "2"
    },
    "market-size": {
      "id": "market-size",
      "name": "Market Size & Opportunity",
      "content": "<p><strong>Total Addressable Market (TAM)</strong></p><p>Global knowledge workers: ~1.25 billion</p><p>Digital note-takers/outliners: ~50-100M active users</p><p>Paying customers in productivity space: ~10-15M</p><p></p><p><strong>Market Growth</strong></p><p>Productivity software market growing at ~12% CAGR</p><p>Remote work acceleration driving tool adoption</p><p>PKM (Personal Knowledge Management) niche exploding</p><p></p><p><strong>Reference Markets</strong></p><p>\u2022 Notion: $10B valuation, 30M+ users (2023)</p><p>\u2022 Obsidian: ~1M users, bootstrapped, sustainable</p><p>\u2022 Roam Research: Raised $9M, struggled with retention</p><p>\u2022 Craft: Raised $40M Series B</p><p>\u2022 Logseq: Open source, 100K+ users</p><p></p><p><strong>Our Slice</strong></p><p>Conservative target: 10,000 paying users in Year 1 = $800K ARR</p><p>Aggressive target: 50,000 paying users in Year 2 = $4M ARR</p>",
      "type": "document",
      "parentId": "market-analysis",
      "childrenIds": [],
      "isCollapsed": false,
      "prefix": "2.1"
    },
    "competitors": {
      "id": "competitors",
      "name": "Competitive Landscape",
      "content": "<p>Detailed competitor analysis</p>",
      "type": "document",
      "parentId": "market-analysis",
      "childrenIds": [
        "comp-notion",
