        "tech-debt"
      ],
      "isCollapsed": false,
      "prefix": "3"
    },
    "product-vision": {
      "id": "product-vision",
      "name": "Product Vision",
      "content": "<p><strong>3-Year Vision</strong></p><p>IdiamPro becomes the default outliner for knowledge workers who value speed and privacy. 100K+ users, sustainable $8-10M ARR, team of 5-8.</p><p></p><p><strong>Core Principles</strong></p><p>1. <strong>Speed above all:</strong> Every interaction should feel instant</p><p>2. <strong>Privacy by default:</strong> Local-first, cloud optional</p><p>3. <strong>Cross-platform parity:</strong> Mobile is not an afterthought</p><p>4. <strong>Data portability:</strong> Users own their data, can export anytime</p><p>5. <strong>Focused scope:</strong> Say no to feature creep, stay an outliner</p><p></p><p><strong>What IdiamPro Will NOT Be</strong></p><p>\u274c An all-in-one workspace (not competing with Notion)</p><p>\u274c A database tool</p><p>\u274c A project management tool (no Gantt charts, sprints)</p><p>\u274c A team collaboration platform (maybe later, but not V1-V2)</p><p>\u274c A social network</p><p></p><p><strong>What IdiamPro COULD Be (Future)</strong></p><p>\u2705 Best-in-class outliner with rich formatting</p><p>\u2705 Personal knowledge base (with backlinks, graph view)</p><p>\u2705 Multi-device sync via cloud (optional)</p><p>\u2705 API for integrations (Zapier, Make)</p><p>\u2705 Publishing tool (export to web, PDF, ePub)</p>",
      "type": "document",
      "parentId": "product-strategy",
      "childrenIds": [],
      "isCollapsed": false,
      "prefix": "3.1"
    },
    "mvp-scope": {
      "id": "mvp-scope",
      "name": "MVP Scope (Launch v1.0)",
      "content": "<p><strong>Status: 95% Complete</strong></p><p></p><p><strong>Must-Have (for launch):</strong></p><p>\u2705 All node types (task, link, code, quote, date, canvas)</p><p>\u2705 Tags & filters</p><p>\u2705 Node colors</p><p>\u2705 Pinning</p><p>\u2705 Multi-select & bulk operations</p><p>\u2705 14 outline templates</p><p>\u2705 Search (NEEDS FIX)</p><p>\u2705 Export/import</p><p>\u2705 iOS gestures optimized</p><p>\u2705 Keyboard shortcuts</p><p>\u274c User accounts (optional for V1)</p><p>\u274c Payment integration (Stripe)</p><p></p><p><strong>Nice-to-Have (can defer):</strong></p><p>\u2022 Breadcrumbs navigation</p><p>\u2022 Node templates (save/reuse subtrees)</p><p>\u2022 Internal node linking [[links]]</p><p>\u2022 Metadata panel (timestamps, word count)</p><p>\u2022 Cloud sync</p>",
      "type": "document",
      "parentId": "product-strategy",
      "childrenIds": [],
      "isCollapsed": false,
      "prefix": "3.2"
    },
    "roadmap-y1": {
      "id": "roadmap-y1",
      "name": "Year 1 Roadmap (Post-Launch)",
      "content": "<p><strong>Q1 2026 (Launch Quarter)</strong></p><p>\u2022 Fix search (critical)</p><p>\u2022 Polish & beta testing</p><p>\u2022 Public launch (ProductHunt, App Store)</p><p>\u2022 Basic payment integration</p><p>Goal: 500 users, 50 paying ($400 MRR)</p><p></p><p><strong>Q2 2026</strong></p><p>\u2022 User accounts & profiles</p><p>\u2022 Cloud backup (optional, encrypted)</p><p>\u2022 Internal node linking [[feature]]</p><p>\u2022 Breadcrumbs navigation</p><p>\u2022 Mobile app polish based on feedback</p><p>Goal: 2,000 users, 200 paying ($1,600 MRR)</p><p></p><p><strong>Q3 2026</strong></p><p>\u2022 Node templates (save/reuse)</p><p>\u2022 Graph view (visual connections)</p><p>\u2022 Publishing: Export to web (public share link)</p><p>\u2022 API v1 (read-only)</p><p>\u2022 Windows app (Electron)</p><p>Goal: 5,000 users, 500 paying ($4,000 MRR)</p><p></p><p><strong>Q4 2026</strong></p><p>\u2022 Collaboration v1 (shared outlines, view-only)</p><p>\u2022 Real-time sync across devices</p><p>\u2022 Mobile widgets (iOS)</p><p>\u2022 Advanced search (regex, filters)</p><p>Goal: 10,000 users, 1,000 paying ($8,000 MRR)</p>",
      "type": "document",
      "parentId": "product-strategy",
      "childrenIds": [],
      "isCollapsed": false,
      "prefix": "3.3"
    },
    "roadmap-y2": {
      "id": "roadmap-y2",
      "name": "Year 2 Roadmap (Growth Phase)",
      "content": "<p><strong>Major Themes</strong></p><p>\u2022 Team collaboration features</p><p>\u2022 API ecosystem (Zapier, webhooks)</p><p>\u2022 Mobile-first workflows</p><p>\u2022 Publishing & sharing tools</p><p></p><p><strong>Potential Features</strong></p><p>\u2022 Comments & discussions</p><p>\u2022 Version history (time machine)</p><p>\u2022 Encrypted cloud storage (E2EE)</p><p>\u2022 Android app</p><p>\u2022 Browser extensions (web clipper)</p><p>\u2022 Integrations (Notion import, Obsidian sync)</p><p>\u2022 AI assistant (summarize, expand ideas)</p><p></p><p>Goal: 50,000 users, 5,000 paying ($40,000 MRR / $480K ARR)</p>",
      "type": "document",
      "parentId": "product-strategy",
      "childrenIds": [],
      "isCollapsed": false,
      "prefix": "3.4"
    },
    "tech-debt": {
      "id": "tech-debt",
      "name": "Technical Debt & Architecture Decisions",
      "content": "<p><strong>Current Tech Stack</strong></p><p>\u2022 Frontend: Next.js 15 + React + TypeScript</p><p>\u2022 Storage: Local (IndexedDB + File System API)</p><p>\u2022 Mobile: Capacitor (iOS native shell)</p><p>\u2022 Desktop: Electron (future)</p><p>\u2022 Styling: Tailwind CSS + shadcn/ui</p><p></p><p><strong>Known Tech Debt</strong></p><p>\u2022 Search implementation needs refactor</p><p>\u2022 State management could use Zustand/Jotai (currently Context API)</p><p>\u2022 File sync logic needs optimization for large outlines</p><p>\u2022 Mobile gestures could be more responsive</p><p></p><p><strong>Architecture Decisions to Make</strong></p><p></p><p><strong>1. Backend: Build or No-Backend?</strong></p><p>Option A: Serverless (Vercel + Supabase/Firebase)</p><p>  Pros: Fast to market, scales automatically, low maintenance</p><p>  Cons: Vendor lock-in, costs scale with users</p><p></p><p>Option B: Self-hosted (Node.js + Postgres + Redis)</p><p>  Pros: Full control, lower long-term costs, better margins</p><p>  Cons: DevOps overhead, slower to ship</p><p></p><p>Recommendation: Start serverless (Supabase), migrate to self-hosted if >10K users</p><p></p><p><strong>2. Sync: CRDT or OT?</strong></p><p>For future real-time collaboration:</p><p>  Option A: CRDT (Yjs, Automerge)</p><p>  Option B: Operational Transform (custom)</p><p></p><p>Recommendation: Use Yjs (proven, good for outlines)</p><p></p><p><strong>3. Offline-First Strategy</strong></p><p>Keep current local-first approach</p><p>Add optional cloud backup (encrypted at rest)</p><p>Sync via background tasks, not blocking UI</p>",
      "type": "document",
      "parentId": "product-strategy",
      "childrenIds": [],
      "isCollapsed": false,
      "prefix": "3.5"
    },
    "business-model": {
      "id": "business-model",
      "name": "Business Model & Pricing",
      "content": "<p>Revenue strategy, pricing psychology, and unit economics</p>",
      "type": "chapter",
      "parentId": "root-planning",
      "childrenIds": [
        "pricing-tiers",
        "pricing-psychology",
        "unit-economics",
        "revenue-streams"
      ],
      "isCollapsed": false,
      "prefix": "4"
    },
    "pricing-tiers": {
      "id": "pricing-tiers",
      "name": "Pricing Tiers (Detailed)",
      "content": "<p><strong>FREE Plan</strong></p><p>\u2022 3 outlines maximum</p><p>\u2022 Unlimited nodes per outline</p><p>\u2022 All features unlocked (tags, colors, code nodes, etc.)</p><p>\u2022 Local storage only</p><p>\u2022 Community support (docs, forum)</p><p>\u2022 IdiamPro branding in exports</p><p></p><p><strong>Rationale:</strong> Generous free tier hooks users, lets them experience full product, removes friction. Most users won't need >3 outlines initially. This is our marketing funnel.</p><p></p><p><strong>PRO Plan - $8/month or $80/year (save $16)</strong></p><p>\u2022 Unlimited outlines</p><p>\u2022 Cloud backup (encrypted, optional)</p><p>\u2022 Sync across devices (web, iOS, desktop)</p><p>\u2022 Priority email support (24h response)</p><p>\u2022 Early access to new features (beta)</p><p>\u2022 Remove branding from exports</p><p>\u2022 Export to additional formats (Markdown, PDF, OPML)</p><p></p><p><strong>Rationale:</strong> $8/mo is sweet spot (cheaper than Notion $10, Roam $15, but premium vs WorkFlowy $5). Annual plan at $80 gives ~17% discount, improves cash flow and retention.</p><p></p><p><strong>TEAM Plan - $15/user/month (Future)</strong></p><p>\u2022 Everything in Pro</p><p>\u2022 Shared outlines (read/write permissions)</p><p>\u2022 Real-time collaboration</p><p>\u2022 Admin dashboard</p><p>\u2022 SSO / SAML (enterprise)</p><p>\u2022 Team billing</p><p></p><p><strong>Rationale:</strong> B2B upsell, higher LTV. Don't launch with this\u2014wait for user demand.</p><p></p><p><strong>LIFETIME Plan - $299 (Limited Offer)</strong></p><p>\u2022 All Pro features forever</p><p>\u2022 Supporter badge</p><p>\u2022 Only during beta/launch (first 1000 customers)</p><p></p><p><strong>Rationale:</strong> Creates urgency, generates cash for runway, builds loyal community. Risk: low recurring revenue, but worth it for early traction.</p>",
      "type": "document",
      "parentId": "business-model",
      "childrenIds": [],
      "isCollapsed": false,
      "prefix": "4.1"
    },
    "pricing-psychology": {
      "id": "pricing-psychology",
      "name": "Pricing Psychology & Anchoring",
      "content": "<p><strong>Price Anchoring Strategy</strong></p><p>Show annual plan first ($80/year = $6.67/mo) to make monthly ($8) seem reasonable.</p><p></p><p>Presentation order on pricing page:</p><p>1. Annual Plan - \"BEST VALUE\" badge</p><p>2. Monthly Plan</p><p>3. Free Plan - \"POPULAR\" badge</p><p></p><p><strong>Competitor Benchmarking</strong></p><p>Position IdiamPro as premium but accessible:</p><p></p><p>$15/mo - Roam Research (too expensive)</p><p>$10/mo - Notion Personal Pro (fair but slow)</p><p>$8/mo - IdiamPro PRO \u2190 Our price</p><p>$5/mo - WorkFlowy Pro (cheap but limited)</p><p>$0 - Obsidian, Logseq (free but technical)</p><p></p><p><strong>Discount Strategy</strong></p><p>\u2022 Student discount: 50% off ($4/mo) with .edu email</p><p>\u2022 Non-profit: 30% off with verification</p><p>\u2022 Black Friday: 40% off annual (one-time)</p><p>\u2022 Referral program: Give 1 month free, get 1 month free</p><p></p><p><strong>Avoid:</strong> Constant sales (devalues product), free trials that expire abruptly (use generous freemium instead)</p>",
      "type": "document",
      "parentId": "business-model",
      "childrenIds": [],
      "isCollapsed": false,
      "prefix": "4.2"
    },
    "unit-economics": {
      "id": "unit-economics",
      "name": "Unit Economics & Projections",
      "content": "<p><strong>Customer Acquisition Cost (CAC)</strong></p><p>Organic (content, SEO, word-of-mouth): $5-20 per user</p><p>Paid (ads, sponsorships): $30-80 per user</p><p></p><p>Target blended CAC: $15-25</p><p></p><p><strong>Lifetime Value (LTV)</strong></p><p>Average subscription length: 18 months (assume 5.5% monthly churn)</p><p>Average revenue per user (ARPU): $8/mo</p><p>Gross margin: 85% (SaaS standard, minimal COGS)</p><p></p><p>LTV = $8 \u00d7 18 months \u00d7 0.85 = $122.40</p><p></p><p><strong>LTV:CAC Ratio</strong></p><p>Target: 3:1 or better</p><p>At $20 CAC \u2192 $122 LTV \u2192 6:1 ratio \u2705 Healthy</p><p>At $50 CAC \u2192 $122 LTV \u2192 2.4:1 ratio \u26a0\ufe0f Marginal</p><p></p><p><strong>Break-Even Point</strong></p><p>Fixed costs (Year 1): ~$50K (hosting, tools, legal)</p><p>Variable costs: ~$1 per paying user (payment processing 3%, hosting)</p><p></p><p>Need ~800 paying users at $8/mo to break even on ops</p><p>Need ~$50K revenue to cover fixed + founder salary (minimal)</p><p></p><p><strong>Revenue Projections (Conservative)</strong></p><p></p><p>Month 3 (post-launch): 500 users, 5% convert \u2192 25 paying \u2192 $200 MRR</p><p>Month 6: 2,000 users, 7% convert \u2192 140 paying \u2192 $1,120 MRR</p><p>Month 12: 10,000 users, 10% convert \u2192 1,000 paying \u2192 $8,000 MRR ($96K ARR)</p><p></p><p><strong>Revenue Projections (Aggressive)</strong></p><p></p><p>Month 12: 50,000 users, 10% convert \u2192 5,000 paying \u2192 $40K MRR ($480K ARR)</p>",
      "type": "document",
      "parentId": "business-model",
      "childrenIds": [],
      "isCollapsed": false,
      "prefix": "4.3"
    },
    "revenue-streams": {
      "id": "revenue-streams",
      "name": "Additional Revenue Streams",
      "content": "<p><strong>Primary: Subscriptions (90% of revenue target)</strong></p><p>Focus here. Everything else is secondary.</p><p></p><p><strong>Secondary Revenue Streams (5-10%)</strong></p><p></p><p><strong>1. Lifetime Licenses</strong></p><p>$299 one-time payment for all Pro features forever</p><p>Offer only during launch window (first 6 months)</p><p>Potential: 100 lifetime sales = $30K</p><p></p><p><strong>2. Template Marketplace (Future)</strong></p><p>Users can sell premium templates</p><p>We take 30% commission</p><p>Potential: Low ($5-10K/year) but builds community</p><p></p><p><strong>3. Enterprise Licensing (Future Y2+)</strong></p><p>Large orgs want on-premise or private cloud</p><p>Custom pricing: $10K-50K/year per org</p><p>Only pursue if inbound interest, don't build speculatively</p><p></p><p><strong>4. API / Developer Platform (Future Y2+)</strong></p><p>Charge for API access (\u00e0 la Notion API)</p><p>Free tier: 100 requests/day</p><p>Paid: $20/mo for 10K requests</p><p>Potential: Modest ($10-20K/year from power users)</p><p></p><p><strong>5. Affiliate / Referral Commissions (Optional)</strong></p><p>Partner with complementary tools (Zapier, Readwise, etc.)</p><p>Small recurring commission</p><p>Potential: Minimal ($1-5K/year)</p><p></p><p><strong>DON'T Pursue (Distractions)</strong></p><p>\u274c Ads (ruins UX, low revenue for niche tools)</p><p>\u274c Selling user data (against privacy values)</p><p>\u274c Consulting / services (doesn't scale)</p><p>\u274c White-label (support burden too high)</p>",
      "type": "document",
      "parentId": "business-model",
      "childrenIds": [],
      "isCollapsed": false,
      "prefix": "4.4"
    },
    "corporate-structure": {
      "id": "corporate-structure",
      "name": "Corporate Structure & Legal",
      "content": "<p>Entity formation, equity, and legal considerations</p>",
      "type": "chapter",
      "parentId": "root-planning",
      "childrenIds": [
        "entity-choice",
        "equity-structure",
        "ip-strategy",
        "compliance"
      ],
      "isCollapsed": false,
      "prefix": "5"
    },
    "entity-choice": {
      "id": "entity-choice",
      "name": "Choosing Business Entity",
      "content": "<p><strong>Option 1: LLC (Limited Liability Company)</strong></p><p></p><p><strong>Pros:</strong></p><p>\u2022 Simple to set up ($100-500)</p><p>\u2022 Pass-through taxation (no double tax)</p><p>\u2022 Flexible ownership structure</p><p>\u2022 Good for solo founder or small team</p><p>\u2022 Low compliance burden</p><p></p><p><strong>Cons:</strong></p><p>\u2022 Not ideal for VC funding (investors prefer C-Corp)</p><p>\u2022 Harder to issue stock options to employees</p><p>\u2022 Some states charge high annual fees (CA: $800/year)</p><p></p><p><strong>Best for:</strong> Bootstrapping, lifestyle business, no VC plans</p><p></p><p><strong>Option 2: C-Corporation</strong></p><p></p><p><strong>Pros:</strong></p><p>\u2022 VC/investor-friendly (can issue preferred stock)</p><p>\u2022 Stock options for employees (ISOs)</p><p>\u2022 Easier to sell company later</p><p>\u2022 Credibility with enterprise customers</p><p></p><p><strong>Cons:</strong></p><p>\u2022 Double taxation (corporate + personal)</p><p>\u2022 More expensive to maintain ($2-5K/year in accounting/legal)</p><p>\u2022 More compliance (board meetings, 83(b) elections, 409A valuations)</p><p></p><p><strong>Best for:</strong> Planning to raise VC, hire team, exit via acquisition</p><p></p><p><strong>Option 3: S-Corporation</strong></p><p></p><p><strong>Pros:</strong></p><p>\u2022 Pass-through taxation like LLC</p><p>\u2022 Saves on self-employment tax vs LLC</p><p></p><p><strong>Cons:</strong></p><p>\u2022 Can't have foreign investors</p><p>\u2022 Max 100 shareholders</p><p>\u2022 One class of stock (no preferred shares)</p><p>\u2022 Not good for VC funding</p><p></p><p><strong>Best for:</strong> Profitable small business with US owners, no VC plans</p><p></p><p>\u2501\u2501\u2501\u2501\u2501\u2501\u2501\u2501\u2501\u2501\u2501\u2501\u2501\u2501\u2501\u2501\u2501</p><p></p><p><strong>RECOMMENDATION FOR IDIAMPRO:</strong></p><p></p><p><strong>Start with Delaware C-Corp</strong></p><p></p><p><strong>Rationale:</strong></p><p>\u2022 Keeps options open for angel/seed funding</p><p>\u2022 Easier to pivot to VC track if product takes off</p><p>\u2022 Professional image for partnerships</p><p>\u2022 Can always stay bootstrapped but have the structure ready</p><p>\u2022 Use Stripe Atlas ($500) or Clerky ($1,000) for easy setup</p><p></p><p>If 100% certain about bootstrapping forever \u2192 LLC is fine, but C-Corp is safer bet.</p>",
      "type": "document",
      "parentId": "corporate-structure",
      "childrenIds": [],
      "isCollapsed": false,
      "prefix": "5.1"
    },
    "equity-structure": {
      "id": "equity-structure",
      "name": "Equity & Ownership Structure",
      "content": "<p><strong>Initial Cap Table (Solo Founder)</strong></p><p></p><p>Founder: 10,000,000 shares (100%)</p><p>Employee pool: 0 shares (set up later if hiring)</p><p>Investors: 0 shares</p><p></p><p>Issue shares at $0.0001/share (par value)</p><p>Total initial investment: $1,000</p><p></p><p><strong>Vesting Schedule for Founder</strong></p><p>Even as solo founder, impose vesting on yourself:</p><p>\u2022 4-year vesting with 1-year cliff</p><p>\u2022 Standard startup structure</p><p></p><p>Why? If you bring on co-founder or raise money later, shows commitment. Also protects company if you leave early.</p><p></p><p><strong>If Adding Co-Founder</strong></p><p></p><p>Split: 50/50 if equal contribution, or 60/40 if one person started earlier</p><p>Both on 4-year vest, 1-year cliff</p><p>Agree on vesting terms in writing BEFORE incorporation</p><p></p><p><strong>Employee Stock Option Pool</strong></p><p></p><p>If hiring team later:</p><p>\u2022 Reserve 10-20% of company for employee options</p><p>\u2022 Create pool before first investor (dilutes founders, not investors)</p><p>\u2022 Use standard 4-year vest, 1-year cliff</p><p>\u2022 Set strike price via 409A valuation (required)</p><p></p><p><strong>Early Employees (First 5)</strong></p><p>\u2022 Engineer #1: 0.5-1.5%</p><p>\u2022 Designer/PM: 0.25-1%</p><p>\u2022 Early contractors: 0.1-0.5%</p><p></p><p><strong>Key Hires Later (Post-Revenue)</strong></p><p>\u2022 VP Engineering: 0.5-1%</p><p>\u2022 Head of Marketing: 0.25-0.75%</p><p></p><p><strong>83(b) Election</strong></p><p>File within 30 days of stock grant</p><p>Pay tax on current value (low) instead of future value (high)</p><p>Critical for founders and early employees</p>",
      "type": "document",
      "parentId": "corporate-structure",
      "childrenIds": [],
      "isCollapsed": false,
      "prefix": "5.2"
    },
    "ip-strategy": {
      "id": "ip-strategy",
      "name": "Intellectual Property Strategy",
      "content": "<p><strong>Trademark</strong></p><p></p><p>File for \"IdiamPro\" trademark:</p><p>\u2022 Class 9: Software</p><p>\u2022 Class 42: SaaS services</p><p></p><p>Cost: $250-350 per class (DIY) or $1,500 (with attorney)</p><p>Timeline: 6-12 months for approval</p><p></p><p>Also consider:</p><p>\u2022 Domain: idiampro.com \u2713</p><p>\u2022 Social handles: @IdiamPro on Twitter, Instagram</p><p>\u2022 Apple Developer Account: IdiamPro LLC/Inc</p><p></p><p><strong>Copyright</strong></p><p></p><p>Automatically own copyright on:</p><p>\u2022 Source code</p><p>\u2022 UI/UX designs</p><p>\u2022 Documentation & content</p><p>\u2022 Marketing materials</p><p></p><p>Optional: Register copyright with US Copyright Office ($65) for stronger legal protection</p><p></p><p><strong>Patents</strong></p><p></p><p>Generally NOT worth it for software:</p><p>\u2022 Expensive ($10-20K per patent)</p><p>\u2022 Hard to defend</p><p>\u2022 Fast-moving industry</p><p></p><p>Only consider if true novel invention (unlikely for outliner)</p><p></p><p><strong>Trade Secrets</strong></p><p></p><p>Keep proprietary:</p><p>\u2022 Core algorithms (if any unique IP)</p><p>\u2022 Customer data & analytics</p><p>\u2022 Business strategies</p><p></p><p>Protect via:</p><p>\u2022 NDAs with contractors/employees</p><p>\u2022 Invention assignment agreements</p><p>\u2022 Secure code repositories (private GitHub)</p><p></p><p><strong>Open Source Considerations</strong></p><p></p><p>IdiamPro is closed-source (for now)</p><p></p><p>Future options:</p><p>\u2022 Open-source the editor core, keep sync/cloud proprietary (like Obsidian model)</p><p>\u2022 Dual-license: AGPLv3 for free, commercial license for businesses</p><p>\u2022 Full open-source if monetization shifts to hosting/support</p><p></p><p>Don't decide yet\u2014keep options open</p>",
      "type": "document",
      "parentId": "corporate-structure",
      "childrenIds": [],
      "isCollapsed": false,
      "prefix": "5.3"
    },
    "compliance": {
      "id": "compliance",
      "name": "Legal Compliance & Governance",
      "content": "<p><strong>Privacy & Data Protection</strong></p><p></p><p><strong>GDPR (EU users):</strong></p><p>\u2022 Transparent privacy policy</p><p>\u2022 User consent for data collection</p><p>\u2022 Right to access, delete, export data</p><p>\u2022 Data breach notification (72 hours)</p><p>\u2022 Appoint DPO if processing large volumes (not needed initially)</p><p></p><p><strong>CCPA (California users):</strong></p><p>\u2022 Disclosure of data collection</p><p>\u2022 Opt-out of data sales (we don't sell data, so easy compliance)</p><p>\u2022 Right to delete</p><p></p><p><strong>IdiamPro advantage:</strong> Local-first model means minimal data collection, easier compliance!</p><p></p><p><strong>Terms of Service Must-Haves</strong></p><p>\u2022 User rights and responsibilities</p><p>\u2022 Acceptable use policy (no illegal content, abuse)</p><p>\u2022 Payment terms (refund policy: 30-day for annual, no refunds for monthly)</p><p>\u2022 Termination rights (we can close accounts for TOS violations)</p><p>\u2022 Limitation of liability</p><p>\u2022 Dispute resolution (arbitration clause)</p><p>\u2022 Jurisdiction (Delaware or your state)</p><p></p><p>Use template + lawyer review ($500-1,500)</p><p></p><p><strong>DMCA Compliance (if user-generated content)</strong></p><p>Appoint DMCA agent with US Copyright Office ($6)</p><p>Set up takedown process for copyright claims</p><p>(Probably not needed unless users share outlines publicly)</p><p></p><p><strong>App Store Compliance</strong></p><p></p><p><strong>Apple App Store:</strong></p><p>\u2022 Privacy labels (what data is collected)</p><p>\u2022 Age rating (probably 4+)</p><p>\u2022 No hidden features or subscriptions</p><p>\u2022 Must use Apple IAP for iOS subscriptions (30% cut)</p><p></p><p><strong>Alternative:</strong> Offer iOS app free, ask users to subscribe via web (avoids Apple's 30%, but can't mention it in-app)</p><p></p><p><strong>Corporate Governance (C-Corp)</strong></p><p></p><p>Annual requirements:</p><p>\u2022 File Delaware franchise tax ($300-500/year)</p><p>\u2022 Hold annual board meeting (even if solo founder)</p><p>\u2022 Keep meeting minutes</p><p>\u2022 File taxes (corporate return + personal)</p><p></p><p><strong>Accounting:</strong></p><p>Use QuickBooks or Wave, hire CPA for tax filing (~$1,500/year)</p>",
      "type": "document",
      "parentId": "corporate-structure",
      "childrenIds": [],
      "isCollapsed": false,
      "prefix": "5.4"
    },
    "funding-strategy": {
      "id": "funding-strategy",
      "name": "Funding Strategy",
      "content": "<p>Bootstrap vs VC, funding scenarios, and investor landscape</p>",
      "type": "chapter",
      "parentId": "root-planning",
      "childrenIds": [
        "bootstrap-case",
        "vc-case",
        "angel-seed",
        "investor-landscape",
        "funding-recommendation"
      ],
      "isCollapsed": false,
      "prefix": "6"
    },
    "bootstrap-case": {
      "id": "bootstrap-case",
      "name": "Case for Bootstrapping",
      "content": "<p><strong>Pros of Bootstrapping</strong></p><p></p><p>\u2705 <strong>Full control:</strong> No board, no pressure to exit, build YOUR vision</p><p>\u2705 <strong>Keep equity:</strong> Own 100% of the company</p><p>\u2705 <strong>Sustainable growth:</strong> Focus on profitability, not vanity metrics</p><p>\u2705 <strong>Lower stress:</strong> No fundraising treadmill, no investor updates</p><p>\u2705 <strong>Lifestyle business option:</strong> $500K-2M ARR can be life-changing income</p><p>\u2705 <strong>Examples:</strong> Obsidian, Superhuman (initially), Basecamp, ConvertKit all bootstrapped</p><p></p><p><strong>Cons of Bootstrapping</strong></p><p></p><p>\u274c <strong>Slower growth:</strong> Can't hire fast, limited marketing budget</p><p>\u274c <strong>Risk of being outpaced:</strong> Funded competitor could move faster</p><p>\u274c <strong>No safety net:</strong> If revenue doesn't materialize, can't sustain team</p><p>\u274c <strong>Harder to attract top talent:</strong> Can't pay high salaries, limited equity value</p><p></p><p><strong>Financial Path (Bootstrap)</strong></p><p></p><p><strong>Year 0 (Pre-Launch):</strong></p><p>\u2022 Personal savings: $20-50K for living expenses while building</p><p>\u2022 Minimal costs: $2-5K (hosting, tools, domain, legal)</p><p></p><p><strong>Year 1:</strong></p><p>\u2022 Reach $96K ARR (1,000 paying users)</p><p>\u2022 Withdraw minimal salary ($40-60K)</p><p>\u2022 Reinvest rest in product & marketing</p><p></p><p><strong>Year 2:</strong></p><p>\u2022 Reach $480K ARR (5,000 paying users)</p><p>\u2022 Salary: $100K</p><p>\u2022 Hire 1-2 contractors (part-time)</p><p></p><p><strong>Year 3:</strong></p><p>\u2022 Reach $1-2M ARR</p><p>\u2022 Hire small team (2-4 FTE)</p><p>\u2022 Profitable, sustainable</p><p></p><p><strong>When Bootstrapping Works Best:</strong></p><p>\u2022 Solo founder or small team</p><p>\u2022 Low burn rate</p><p>\u2022 Market doesn't require blitz-scaling</p><p>\u2022 Product can reach profitability in 12-18 months</p><p>\u2022 Founder values independence over growth-at-all-costs</p>",
      "type": "document",
      "parentId": "funding-strategy",
      "childrenIds": [],
      "isCollapsed": false,
      "prefix": "6.1"
    },
    "vc-case": {
      "id": "vc-case",
      "name": "Case for Venture Capital",
      "content": "<p><strong>Pros of Raising VC</strong></p><p></p><p>\u2705 <strong>Fuel for growth:</strong> Hire team, scale marketing, build faster</p><p>\u2705 <strong>Network & expertise:</strong> VCs bring connections, advice, recruiting help</p><p>\u2705 <strong>Validation:</strong> Raises profile, easier to hire and partner</p><p>\u2705 <strong>Bigger outcome potential:</strong> Swing for $100M+ exit vs $10M lifestyle business</p><p>\u2705 <strong>Safety net:</strong> Runway to experiment, pivot, recover from mistakes</p><p></p><p><strong>Cons of Raising VC</strong></p><p></p><p>\u274c <strong>Loss of control:</strong> Board seats, investor pressure, can be fired</p><p>\u274c <strong>Dilution:</strong> Own 50-70% after Seed, 20-40% by Series B</p><p>\u274c <strong>Growth pressure:</strong> Must scale fast or die (10x revenue YoY expected)</p><p>\u274c <strong>Exit pressure:</strong> VCs need liquidity in 7-10 years, forces sale/IPO</p><p>\u274c <strong>Time sink:</strong> Fundraising takes 3-6 months, distracts from building</p><p>\u274c <strong>Wrong incentives:</strong> Optimize for valuation, not profitability</p><p></p><p><strong>VC Funding Stages</strong></p><p></p><p><strong>Pre-Seed ($100K-500K):</strong></p><p>\u2022 Accelerators (Y Combinator, Techstars)</p><p>\u2022 Angel investors</p><p>\u2022 Friends & family</p><p>\u2022 At idea or prototype stage</p><p>\u2022 Dilution: ~5-10%</p><p></p><p><strong>Seed ($500K-2M):</strong></p><p>\u2022 Early-stage VCs (Hustle Fund, Weekend Fund, Uncork)</p><p>\u2022 Super angels</p><p>\u2022 Product launched, some early users (1K-10K)</p><p>\u2022 Dilution: ~15-25%</p><p></p><p><strong>Series A ($2M-10M):</strong></p><p>\u2022 Traditional VCs (a16z, Sequoia, Accel, etc.)</p><p>\u2022 Strong product-market fit</p><p>\u2022 $500K-2M ARR, 30%+ MoM growth</p><p>\u2022 Dilution: ~20-30%</p><p></p><p><strong>When VC Makes Sense:</strong></p><p>\u2022 Winner-take-all market (need to move FAST)</p><p>\u2022 High CAC requires upfront capital</p><p>\u2022 Network effects (collaboration features)</p><p>\u2022 Team of 2-3+ co-founders</p><p>\u2022 Willing to sell company in 5-10 years</p>",
      "type": "document",
      "parentId": "funding-strategy",
      "childrenIds": [],
      "isCollapsed": false,
      "prefix": "6.2"
    },
    "angel-seed": {
      "id": "angel-seed",
      "name": "Angel / Seed Round Strategy",
      "content": "<p><strong>If Raising $100K-500K Angel/Seed</strong></p><p></p><p><strong>When to Raise:</strong></p><p>\u2022 After launch</p><p>\u2022 500-2,000 users, growing 20%+ MoM</p><p>\u2022 $5-20K MRR</p><p>\u2022 Clear product-market fit signals</p><p></p><p><strong>What to Offer:</strong></p><p>\u2022 $100-500K total</p><p>\u2022 SAFE or convertible note (standard YC terms)</p><p>\u2022 $2-5M valuation cap</p><p>\u2022 20% discount on Series A</p><p>\u2022 Dilution: ~5-15%</p><p></p><p><strong>Use of Funds:</strong></p><p>\u2022 60% - Team (hire 1-2 engineers, designer, or marketer)</p><p>\u2022 20% - Marketing (ads, content, ProductHunt sponsor)</p><p>\u2022 10% - Infrastructure (cloud hosting, better tools)</p><p>\u2022 10% - Buffer (legal, unexpected costs)</p><p></p><p>Runway: 12-18 months</p><p></p><p><strong>Target Angels:</strong></p><p>\u2022 Productivity tool founders (Superhuman, Notion, Obsidian community)</p><p>\u2022 SaaS angels on AngelList</p><p>\u2022 YC partners / alumni</p><p>\u2022 Tech influencers who love tools</p><p></p><p><strong>Pitch Deck (10 slides):</strong></p><p>1. Cover (logo, tagline)</p><p>2. Problem (note-taking/outlining is broken)</p><p>3. Solution (IdiamPro in 1 sentence + demo screenshot)</p><p>4. Product (features, screenshots)</p><p>5. Traction (users, growth, revenue, testimonials)</p><p>6. Market (TAM, competition, positioning)</p><p>7. Business Model (pricing, unit economics)</p><p>8. Roadmap (next 12 months)</p><p>9. Team (founder background, why you?)</p><p>10. Ask ($XXXk, use of funds, timeline to profitability)</p><p></p><p><strong>Fundraising Timeline:</strong></p><p>Week 1-2: Build deck, financial model</p><p>Week 3-4: Warm intros to 20-30 angels</p><p>Week 5-8: Pitch meetings, follow-ups</p><p>Week 9-10: Term sheets, negotiate, close</p><p></p><p>Total: ~3 months (part-time, while running product)</p>",
      "type": "document",
      "parentId": "funding-strategy",
      "childrenIds": [],
      "isCollapsed": false,
      "prefix": "6.3"
    },
    "investor-landscape": {
      "id": "investor-landscape",
      "name": "Investor Landscape (Productivity SaaS)",
      "content": "<p><strong>Angel Investors (Productivity Space)</strong></p><p>\u2022 Tiago Forte (Building a Second Brain)</p><p>\u2022 Nat Eliason (ex-Roam)</p><p>\u2022 Steph Smith (a16z, productivity writer)</p><p>\u2022 David Perell (Write of Passage)</p><p>\u2022 Lenny Rachitsky (Lenny's Newsletter)</p><p></p><p><strong>Micro VCs / Scout Programs</strong></p><p>\u2022 Hustle Fund (seed-stage, fast decisions)</p><p>\u2022 Weekend Fund (fast yes/no)</p><p>\u2022 Tiny Seed (bootstrapper-friendly fund)</p><p>\u2022 Earnest Capital (profit-focused, not exit-focused)</p><p>\u2022 YC Scout Program (ask YC alums to scout you)</p><p></p><p><strong>Seed Funds (If Strong Traction)</strong></p><p>\u2022 Craft Ventures (SaaS focus, invested in Notion competitor Coda)</p><p>\u2022 GGV Capital (productivity tools)</p><p>\u2022 General Catalyst (early Notion investor)</p><p>\u2022 Index Ventures (Figma, Notion)</p><p></p><p><strong>Alternative: Revenue-Based Financing</strong></p><p>Non-dilutive capital (no equity given up):</p><p>\u2022 Clearco (formerly Clearbanco)</p><p>\u2022 Pipe</p><p>\u2022 Lighter Capital</p><p></p><p>How it works:</p><p>\u2022 Borrow $50-500K</p><p>\u2022 Repay as % of monthly revenue (e.g., 5-10%)</p><p>\u2022 Pay back 1.3-1.5x borrowed amount</p><p>\u2022 Good if you have $20K+ MRR and need growth capital without dilution</p>",
      "type": "document",
      "parentId": "funding-strategy",
      "childrenIds": [],
      "isCollapsed": false,
      "prefix": "6.4"
    },
    "funding-recommendation": {
      "id": "funding-recommendation",
      "name": "Funding Recommendation for IdiamPro",
      "content": "<p><strong>RECOMMENDED PATH: Bootstrap \u2192 Opportunistic Angel</strong></p><p></p><p><strong>Phase 1: Bootstrap (Months 1-6)</strong></p><p>\u2022 Launch with own capital</p><p>\u2022 Validate product-market fit</p><p>\u2022 Get to $5-10K MRR organically</p><p>\u2022 Prove you can grow without funding</p><p></p><p><strong>Why:</strong> You're solo founder, product is 95% done, market doesn't require blitz-scaling. Bootstrap proves the model works.</p><p></p><p><strong>Phase 2: Evaluate Options (Months 6-9)</strong></p><p></p><p><strong>If traction is strong (>$10K MRR, 30%+ MoM growth):</strong></p><p>\u2022 Consider raising $200-500K angel/seed</p><p>\u2022 Use to hire 2-3 people, accelerate growth</p><p>\u2022 Target: $1M ARR by end of Year 1</p><p></p><p><strong>If traction is modest (<$10K MRR, 10-20% growth):</strong></p><p>\u2022 Keep bootstrapping</p><p>\u2022 Focus on profitability, not growth at all costs</p><p>\u2022 Lifestyle business is great outcome ($500K-1M/year personally)</p><p></p><p><strong>Phase 3: Series A Decision (Year 2+)</strong></p><p></p><p>Only raise institutional VC if:</p><p>\u2022 $1M+ ARR</p><p>\u2022 3-5x YoY growth</p><p>\u2022 Clear path to $10M+ ARR</p><p>\u2022 Market leader potential</p><p></p><p>Otherwise, stay bootstrapped and profitable.</p><p></p><p>\u2501\u2501\u2501\u2501\u2501\u2501\u2501\u2501\u2501\u2501\u2501\u2501\u2501\u2501\u2501\u2501\u2501</p><p></p><p><strong>TLDR: Start bootstrapped. If product explodes, raise smart angel money. Don't raise VC unless you're clearly winning big.</strong></p>",
      "type": "document",
      "parentId": "funding-strategy",
      "childrenIds": [],
      "isCollapsed": false,
      "prefix": "6.5",
      "metadata": {
        "color": "green"
      }
    },
    "gtm-strategy": {
      "id": "gtm-strategy",
      "name": "Go-to-Market Strategy",
      "content": "<p>How to acquire first 1000 customers</p>",
      "type": "chapter",
      "parentId": "root-planning",
      "childrenIds": [
        "gtm-channels",
        "gtm-launch",
        "gtm-growth",
        "gtm-retention"
      ],
      "isCollapsed": false,
      "prefix": "7"
    },
    "gtm-channels": {
      "id": "gtm-channels",
      "name": "Customer Acquisition Channels",
      "content": "<p><strong>Tier 1 Channels (Highest Priority)</strong></p><p></p><p><strong>1. ProductHunt Launch</strong></p><p>\u2022 Potential reach: 10K-50K visitors on launch day</p><p>\u2022 Target: Top 5 product of the day</p><p>\u2022 Expect: 500-2,000 signups, 5-10% convert to paying</p><p>\u2022 One-time spike, but great for initial traction + credibility</p><p></p><p><strong>2. Content Marketing (SEO Blog)</strong></p><p>\u2022 Write 2-4 blog posts/month on idiampro.com/blog</p><p>\u2022 Target keywords: \"best outliner app\", \"Notion alternative\", \"local-first note-taking\"</p><p>\u2022 Long-tail: \"how to outline a book\", \"project planning template\"</p><p>\u2022 Timeline: 3-6 months to see organic traffic</p><p>\u2022 Potential: 1K-5K organic visits/month by Month 6</p><p></p><p><strong>3. Reddit / Community Marketing</strong></p><p>\u2022 r/productivity (3M members)</p><p>\u2022 r/GettingThingsGTD (50K)</p><p>\u2022 r/ObsidianMD (200K)</p><p>\u2022 r/selfhosted (500K)</p><p>\u2022 Be helpful first, mention IdiamPro naturally</p><p>\u2022 Post \"Show & Tell\" every few months</p><p></p><p><strong>4. Twitter / X Presence</strong></p><p>\u2022 Build in public (share progress, learnings)</p><p>\u2022 Engage with productivity community</p><p>\u2022 Share tips, shortcuts, use cases</p><p>\u2022 Target: 1K followers by Month 6</p><p></p><p><strong>Tier 2 Channels (Medium Priority)</strong></p><p></p><p><strong>5. YouTube Tutorials</strong></p><p>\u2022 \"How to use IdiamPro\" walkthrough</p><p>\u2022 Comparison videos (vs Notion, WorkFlowy, Obsidian)</p><p>\u2022 Partner with productivity YouTubers (sponsored reviews)</p><p></p><p><strong>6. App Store Optimization (ASO)</strong></p><p>\u2022 Optimize iOS App Store listing</p><p>\u2022 Keywords: outliner, note-taking, productivity</p><p>\u2022 Get initial reviews (ask beta users)</p><p>\u2022 Potential: 100-500 organic downloads/month</p><p></p><p><strong>7. Email Newsletter</strong></p><p>\u2022 Weekly tips for outline mastery</p><p>\u2022 Build email list via lead magnet (free template pack)</p><p>\u2022 Promote new features, success stories</p><p></p><p><strong>Tier 3 Channels (Test Later)</strong></p><p></p><p><strong>8. Paid Ads (Google, Facebook)</strong></p><p>\u2022 Only after organic channels proven</p><p>\u2022 Start with $500/month budget</p><p>\u2022 Target: CAC < $30</p><p></p><p><strong>9. Podcast Sponsorships</strong></p><p>\u2022 Sponsor productivity podcasts</p><p>\u2022 Cost: $500-2,000/episode</p><p>\u2022 Only if CAC math works</p><p></p><p><strong>10. Affiliate Program</strong></p><p>\u2022 Pay 20-30% commission to affiliates</p><p>\u2022 Recruit productivity bloggers, YouTubers</p><p></p><p><strong>DON'T Waste Time On:</strong></p><p>\u274c Cold email outreach (too spammy for B2C)</p><p>\u274c LinkedIn ads (expensive, wrong audience)</p><p>\u274c Trade shows / conferences (too expensive for early stage)</p>",
      "type": "document",
      "parentId": "gtm-strategy",
      "childrenIds": [],
      "isCollapsed": false,
      "prefix": "7.1"
    },
    "gtm-launch": {
      "id": "gtm-launch",
      "name": "Launch Playbook (First 30 Days)",
      "content": "<p><strong>Pre-Launch (2 weeks before)</strong></p><p>\u2022 Build email waitlist (100-500 people)</p><p>\u2022 Set up ProductHunt account, get hunter</p><p>\u2022 Prepare launch assets (screenshots, video, social posts)</p><p>\u2022 Reach out to ProductHunt voting squad</p><p>\u2022 Write launch blog post</p><p>\u2022 Prepare launch email to waitlist</p><p></p><p><strong>Launch Day (Day 1)</strong></p><p>\u2022 Go live on ProductHunt at 12:01am PST</p><p>\u2022 Post to Twitter, LinkedIn, Reddit (carefully)</p><p>\u2022 Email waitlist (stagger over 3 hours)</p><p>\u2022 Respond to EVERY ProductHunt comment</p><p>\u2022 Monitor upvotes, share milestones (#3 product! #1 product!)</p><p>\u2022 Post in Indie Hackers</p><p></p><p>Goal: Top 5 product of the day, 1,000+ visits, 100+ signups</p><p></p><p><strong>Week 1 (Days 2-7)</strong></p><p>\u2022 Follow up with signups (welcome email sequence)</p><p>\u2022 Post \"We launched!\" recap on blog</p><p>\u2022 Share to HackerNews (Show HN)</p><p>\u2022 Reach out to tech journalists (TechCrunch, The Verge - unlikely but try)</p><p>\u2022 Post in niche subreddits</p><p>\u2022 Ask for feedback in-app</p><p></p><p>Goal: 500 total users</p><p></p><p><strong>Week 2-4 (Days 8-30)</strong></p><p>\u2022 Start content marketing (first 2 blog posts)</p><p>\u2022 Launch referral program (give 1 month Pro, get 1 month Pro)</p><p>\u2022 Collect testimonials from happy users</p><p>\u2022 Fix top bugs reported</p><p>\u2022 Announce first update (\"We shipped your feedback!\")</p><p>\u2022 Plan ProductHunt Ship for ongoing updates</p><p></p><p>Goal: 1,000 total users, 50 paying ($400 MRR)</p>",
      "type": "document",
      "parentId": "gtm-strategy",
      "childrenIds": [],
      "isCollapsed": false,
      "prefix": "7.2"
    },
    "gtm-growth": {
      "id": "gtm-growth",
      "name": "Growth Loops & Viral Mechanics",
      "content": "<p><strong>Built-in Growth Mechanisms</strong></p><p></p><p><strong>1. Referral Program</strong></p><p>Give 1 month Pro, Get 1 month Pro</p><p>Prompt after user creates 3rd outline</p><p></p><p><strong>2. Export Branding (Free Tier)</strong></p><p>Add \"Created with IdiamPro\" footer on exports</p><p>Links to idiampro.com</p><p>Remove for Pro users</p><p></p><p><strong>3. Public Sharing (Future)</strong></p><p>Allow users to publish outlines to web</p><p>Each shared outline = mini landing page for IdiamPro</p><p>Example: idiampro.com/share/abc123</p><p></p><p><strong>4. Template Marketplace (Future)</strong></p><p>Users share templates publicly</p><p>Non-users can download \u2192 prompted to sign up</p><p></p><p><strong>5. Collaboration (Future)</strong></p><p>Invite teammates to shared outline</p><p>Each invite = new potential customer</p><p></p><p><strong>Word-of-Mouth Drivers</strong></p><p></p><p>\u2022 Fast performance (\"Try this, it's so fast!\")</p><p>\u2022 Beautiful UI (\"Look at this app\")</p><p>\u2022 Unique features (\"You can create a canvas node!\")</p><p>\u2022 Privacy story (\"Finally, an app that doesn't spy on me\")</p><p></p><p><strong>North Star Metric</strong></p><p></p><p>Track: <strong>Weekly Active Outliners (WAO)</strong></p><p></p><p>Definition: Users who edit an outline at least once per week</p><p></p><p>Why: Leading indicator of engagement \u2192 retention \u2192 revenue</p><p></p><p>Target:</p><p>\u2022 Month 1: 100 WAO</p><p>\u2022 Month 3: 500 WAO</p><p>\u2022 Month 6: 2,000 WAO</p><p>\u2022 Month 12: 10,000 WAO</p>",
      "type": "document",
      "parentId": "gtm-strategy",
      "childrenIds": [],
      "isCollapsed": false,
      "prefix": "7.3"
    },
    "gtm-retention": {
      "id": "gtm-retention",
      "name": "Retention & Churn Strategy",
      "content": "<p><strong>Activation (Day 1)</strong></p><p></p><p>Goal: Get user to create first outline in first session</p><p></p><p>Tactics:</p><p>\u2022 Show empty state with templates (done \u2713)</p><p>\u2022 Onboarding tooltip tour (optional)</p><p>\u2022 \"Create your first outline\" CTA</p><p></p><p>Success metric: 60%+ create outline on Day 1</p><p></p><p><strong>Engagement (Week 1)</strong></p><p></p><p>Goal: Get user to create 3+ outlines, use 3+ features</p><p></p><p>Tactics:</p><p>\u2022 Email: \"5 ways to use IdiamPro\"</p><p>\u2022 In-app: \"Try creating a task node!\"</p><p>\u2022 Highlight keyboard shortcuts</p><p></p><p>Success metric: 40%+ return on Day 3, 7</p><p></p><p><strong>Habit Formation (Month 1)</strong></p><p></p><p>Goal: Daily or weekly usage habit</p><p></p><p>Tactics:</p><p>\u2022 Email tips (\"How to organize research with tags\")</p><p>\u2022 Show usage stats (\"You created 12 nodes this week!\")</p><p>\u2022 Prompt to upgrade (\"You have 3 outlines, upgrade for unlimited\")</p><p></p><p>Success metric: 30%+ become weekly active</p><p></p><p><strong>Churn Prevention</strong></p><p></p><p><strong>Identify At-Risk Users:</strong></p><p>\u2022 Haven't logged in for 7 days</p><p>\u2022 Created only 1 outline</p><p>\u2022 No activity after Day 1</p><p></p><p><strong>Re-engagement Campaigns:</strong></p><p>\u2022 Email: \"We miss you! Here's a new template\"</p><p>\u2022 Offer: Free 1-month trial of Pro features</p><p>\u2022 Survey: \"Why did you stop using IdiamPro?\"</p><p></p><p><strong>Churn Analysis (Paying Users)</strong></p><p></p><p>Track why users cancel:</p><p>\u2022 Pricing too high?</p><p>\u2022 Missing features?</p><p>\u2022 Switched to competitor?</p><p>\u2022 Not using enough?</p><p></p><p>Exit survey on cancellation</p><p>Offer discount to stay (1 time only)</p><p></p><p><strong>Target Metrics</strong></p><p></p><p>\u2022 Day 1 activation: 60%+</p><p>\u2022 Day 7 retention: 40%+</p><p>\u2022 Day 30 retention: 25%+</p><p>\u2022 Monthly churn (paying): <5%</p>",
      "type": "document",
      "parentId": "gtm-strategy",
      "childrenIds": [],
      "isCollapsed": false,
      "prefix": "7.4"
    },
    "financials": {
      "id": "financials",
      "name": "Financial Projections",
      "content": "<p>Revenue, costs, and path to profitability</p>",
      "type": "chapter",
      "parentId": "root-planning",
      "childrenIds": [
        "revenue-model",
        "cost-structure",
        "profitability-timeline",
        "financial-scenarios"
      ],
      "isCollapsed": false,
      "prefix": "8"
    },
    "revenue-model": {
      "id": "revenue-model",
      "name": "Revenue Model & Assumptions",
      "content": "<p><strong>Pricing</strong></p><p>\u2022 Free: 3 outlines</p><p>\u2022 Pro: $8/month or $80/year</p><p>\u2022 Team: $15/user/month (future)</p><p></p><p><strong>Conversion Assumptions</strong></p><p></p><p>Free \u2192 Pro: 5-10% (industry standard for freemium)</p><p>Monthly vs Annual: 30% choose annual (2.5x monthly revenue upfront)</p><p></p><p><strong>Blended ARPU (Average Revenue Per User)</strong></p><p></p><p>70% monthly \u00d7 $8 = $5.60</p><p>30% annual \u00d7 $6.67 = $2.00</p><p>Blended ARPU \u2248 $7.60/month</p><p></p><p>(Using $8 for simplicity in projections)</p><p></p><p><strong>Churn Assumptions</strong></p><p></p><p>Monthly subscribers: 8% monthly churn (avg lifetime 12 months)</p><p>Annual subscribers: 30% yearly churn (avg lifetime 3+ years)</p><p>Blended: ~5.5% monthly churn</p><p></p><p><strong>Growth Assumptions</strong></p><p></p><p>Conservative:</p><p>\u2022 Month 1-3: 50% MoM user growth</p><p>\u2022 Month 4-6: 30% MoM</p><p>\u2022 Month 7-12: 20% MoM</p><p></p><p>Aggressive:</p><p>\u2022 Month 1-6: 100% MoM</p><p>\u2022 Month 7-12: 50% MoM</p>",
      "type": "document",
      "parentId": "financials",
      "childrenIds": [],
      "isCollapsed": false,
      "prefix": "8.1"
    },
    "cost-structure": {
      "id": "cost-structure",
      "name": "Cost Structure & Burn Rate",
      "content": "<p><strong>Fixed Costs (Monthly)</strong></p><p></p><p><strong>Pre-Revenue:</strong></p><p>\u2022 Domain & hosting: $50</p><p>\u2022 Tools (Vercel, Supabase, email): $100</p><p>\u2022 Legal / accounting: $200 (amortized)</p><p>Total: ~$350/month</p><p></p><p><strong>Post-Launch (Year 1):</strong></p><p>\u2022 Hosting (scales with users): $200-1,000</p><p>\u2022 Tools & SaaS: $300-500</p><p>\u2022 Payment processing (Stripe 3%): $XXX (variable)</p><p>\u2022 Marketing: $500-2,000</p><p>\u2022 Legal / accounting: $300</p><p>\u2022 Insurance: $100</p><p>Total: ~$1,400 - $4,000/month</p><p></p><p><strong>Variable Costs (Per Paying User)</strong></p><p>\u2022 Payment processing (Stripe): 3% = $0.24/user/month</p><p>\u2022 Cloud hosting: ~$0.10/user/month</p><p>\u2022 Email (SendGrid): ~$0.05/user/month</p><p>Total: ~$0.40/user/month</p><p></p><p>Gross Margin: ($8 - $0.40) / $8 = 95% \ud83d\ude80</p><p></p><p>(SaaS typically 80-90%, we're high because of local-first architecture)</p><p></p><p><strong>Team Costs (If Hiring)</strong></p><p></p><p>Contractor (part-time):</p><p>\u2022 Engineer: $5-10K/month</p><p>\u2022 Designer: $3-7K/month</p><p>\u2022 Marketer: $3-5K/month</p><p></p><p>Full-Time Employee:</p><p>\u2022 Engineer: $120-180K/year ($10-15K/month)</p><p>\u2022 Designer: $90-140K/year</p><p>\u2022 PM/Marketer: $80-120K/year</p><p></p><p>Burn with 2 FTEs: ~$20-30K/month</p>",
      "type": "document",
      "parentId": "financials",
      "childrenIds": [],
      "isCollapsed": false,
      "prefix": "8.2"
    },
    "profitability-timeline": {
      "id": "profitability-timeline",
      "name": "Path to Profitability",
      "content": "<p><strong>Break-Even Analysis</strong></p><p></p><p><strong>Scenario 1: Solo Founder, Minimal Costs</strong></p><p></p><p>Monthly fixed costs: $2,000</p><p>Revenue per paying user: $8</p><p>Gross margin: 95% \u2192 $7.60 profit per user</p><p></p><p>Break-even: $2,000 / $7.60 = 264 paying users</p><p></p><p>At 10% conversion \u2192 need 2,640 total users</p><p></p><p><strong>Timeline: Month 3-4 (realistic)</strong></p><p></p><p><strong>Scenario 2: With Team (2 FTEs)</strong></p><p></p><p>Monthly costs: $25,000</p><p>Break-even: $25,000 / $7.60 = 3,290 paying users \u2192 $26,320 MRR</p><p></p><p>At 10% conversion \u2192 need 32,900 total users</p><p></p><p><strong>Timeline: Month 12-18 (if growth is strong)</strong></p><p></p><p><strong>Profitability Milestones (Solo, Bootstrap)</strong></p><p></p><p><strong>Month 3:</strong> 264 paying users \u2192 $2,112 MRR \u2192 Break-even</p><p><strong>Month 6:</strong> 500 paying users \u2192 $4,000 MRR \u2192 $2K profit/month</p><p><strong>Month 12:</strong> 1,000 paying users \u2192 $8,000 MRR \u2192 $6K profit/month</p><p><strong>Month 24:</strong> 5,000 paying users \u2192 $40,000 MRR \u2192 $38K profit/month</p><p></p><p>Year 2 profit = $456K (life-changing income for solo founder)</p>",
      "type": "document",
      "parentId": "financials",
      "childrenIds": [],
      "isCollapsed": false,
      "prefix": "8.3"
    },
    "financial-scenarios": {
      "id": "financial-scenarios",
      "name": "3-Year Financial Scenarios",
      "content": "<p><strong>Conservative Scenario (Bootstrap)</strong></p><p></p><p><strong>Year 1:</strong></p><p>\u2022 Users: 10,000 (end of year)</p><p>\u2022 Paying: 1,000 (10% conversion)</p><p>\u2022 MRR: $8,000</p><p>\u2022 ARR: $96,000</p><p>\u2022 Costs: $24K</p><p>\u2022 Profit: $72K</p><p></p><p><strong>Year 2:</strong></p><p>\u2022 Users: 50,000</p><p>\u2022 Paying: 5,000</p><p>\u2022 MRR: $40,000</p><p>\u2022 ARR: $480,000</p><p>\u2022 Costs: $50K (hired 1 contractor)</p><p>\u2022 Profit: $430K</p><p></p><p><strong>Year 3:</strong></p><p>\u2022 Users: 150,000</p><p>\u2022 Paying: 15,000</p><p>\u2022 MRR: $120,000</p><p>\u2022 ARR: $1,440,000</p><p>\u2022 Costs: $300K (2 FTEs)</p><p>\u2022 Profit: $1,140K</p><p></p><p>\u2501\u2501\u2501\u2501\u2501\u2501\u2501\u2501\u2501\u2501\u2501\u2501\u2501\u2501\u2501\u2501\u2501</p><p></p><p><strong>Moderate Scenario (Angel Funded)</strong></p><p></p><p>Raise $300K angel in Month 6</p><p></p><p><strong>Year 1:</strong></p><p>\u2022 Users: 25,000</p><p>\u2022 Paying: 2,500</p><p>\u2022 MRR: $20,000</p><p>\u2022 ARR: $240,000</p><p>\u2022 Costs: $180K (2 FTEs hired after funding)</p><p>\u2022 Burn: $60K (covered by angel round)</p><p></p><p><strong>Year 2:</strong></p><p>\u2022 Users: 150,000</p><p>\u2022 Paying: 15,000</p><p>\u2022 MRR: $120,000</p><p>\u2022 ARR: $1,440,000</p><p>\u2022 Costs: $600K (5 FTEs)</p><p>\u2022 Profit: $840K</p><p></p><p><strong>Year 3:</strong></p><p>\u2022 Users: 500,000</p><p>\u2022 Paying: 50,000</p><p>\u2022 MRR: $400,000</p><p>\u2022 ARR: $4,800,000</p><p>\u2022 Costs: $2M (15 FTEs)</p><p>\u2022 Profit: $2.8M</p><p></p><p>\u2501\u2501\u2501\u2501\u2501\u2501\u2501\u2501\u2501\u2501\u2501\u2501\u2501\u2501\u2501\u2501\u2501</p><p></p><p><strong>Aggressive Scenario (VC-Backed)</strong></p><p></p><p>Raise $2M Seed in Month 9</p><p></p><p><strong>Year 1:</strong></p><p>\u2022 Users: 50,000</p><p>\u2022 Paying: 5,000</p><p>\u2022 ARR: $480,000</p><p>\u2022 Burn: $800K (hiring, marketing)</p><p></p><p><strong>Year 2:</strong></p><p>\u2022 Users: 500,000</p><p>\u2022 Paying: 50,000</p><p>\u2022 ARR: $4,800,000</p><p>\u2022 Burn: $3M (aggressive team building)</p><p>\u2022 Profit: $1.8M</p><p></p><p><strong>Year 3:</strong></p><p>\u2022 Users: 2,000,000</p><p>\u2022 Paying: 200,000</p><p>\u2022 ARR: $19,200,000</p><p>\u2022 Costs: $10M</p><p>\u2022 Profit: $9.2M</p><p>\u2022 Raise Series A at $100M valuation</p>",
      "type": "document",
      "parentId": "financials",
      "childrenIds": [],
      "isCollapsed": false,
      "prefix": "8.4",
      "metadata": {
        "color": "blue"
      }
    },
    "team-hiring": {
      "id": "team-hiring",
      "name": "Team & Hiring Strategy",
      "content": "<p>When and how to build the team</p>",
      "type": "chapter",
      "parentId": "root-planning",
      "childrenIds": [
        "hiring-plan",
        "key-roles",
        "culture"
      ],
      "isCollapsed": false,
      "prefix": "9"
    },
    "hiring-plan": {
      "id": "hiring-plan",
      "name": "Hiring Roadmap",
      "content": "<p><strong>Phase 1: Solo (Months 1-6)</strong></p><p></p><p>Stay solo through launch and early traction</p><p></p><p>Outsource:</p><p>\u2022 Logo design (Fiverr, $50-200)</p><p>\u2022 Legal docs (Clerky, $1K)</p><p>\u2022 Accounting (CPA, $1,500/year)</p><p></p><p><strong>Phase 2: First Hires (Months 6-12)</strong></p><p></p><p>Only hire if revenue supports it ($10K+ MRR)</p><p></p><p><strong>Hire #1: Full-Stack Engineer (contract \u2192 FTE)</strong></p><p>Why: Speed up development, ship features faster</p><p>Skills: React, TypeScript, Node.js, mobile (Capacitor)</p><p>Comp: $5-10K/month contract, or $140K/year FTE + 0.5-1% equity</p><p></p><p><strong>Hire #2: Product Designer / UI-UX</strong></p><p>Why: Polish the product, improve onboarding, marketing site</p><p>Skills: Figma, design systems, mobile UX</p><p>Comp: $4-7K/month contract, or $120K/year + 0.5% equity</p><p></p><p><strong>Phase 3: Growth Team (Year 2)</strong></p><p></p><p>Once product-market fit is clear ($50K+ MRR)</p><p></p><p><strong>Hire #3: Marketing / Growth Lead</strong></p><p>Why: Scale customer acquisition beyond founder-led</p><p>Skills: Content, SEO, paid ads, email marketing</p><p>Comp: $100K + 0.5% equity</p><p></p><p><strong>Hire #4: Customer Success / Support</strong></p><p>Why: Handle support load, reduce churn</p><p>Skills: Empathy, product knowledge, writing</p><p>Comp: $60-80K + 0.25% equity</p><p></p><p><strong>Phase 4: Scale Team (Year 2-3)</strong></p><p></p><p><strong>Hire #5-8: Additional Engineers</strong></p><p>Mobile specialist, backend, infra</p><p></p><p><strong>Hire #9: Head of Product / PM</strong></p><p>Take over product roadmap, let founder focus on strategy</p><p></p><p><strong>Hire #10-12: Sales / Business Development (if B2B pivot)</strong></p><p></p><p><strong>Remote-First or In-Person?</strong></p><p></p><p>Recommend: <strong>Remote-first</strong></p><p>\u2022 Access global talent</p><p>\u2022 Lower costs</p><p>\u2022 Flexible for early-stage</p><p>\u2022 Use tools: Slack, Linear, Figma, Loom</p><p></p><p>Optional: Offsite twice/year for team bonding</p>",
      "type": "document",
      "parentId": "team-hiring",
      "childrenIds": [],
      "isCollapsed": false,
      "prefix": "9.1"
    },
    "key-roles": {
      "id": "key-roles",
      "name": "Key Roles & Responsibilities",
      "content": "<p><strong>Founder (You)</strong></p><p>\u2022 Product vision</p><p>\u2022 Engineering (initially)</p><p>\u2022 Fundraising (if applicable)</p><p>\u2022 Customer development</p><p>\u2022 Marketing & sales (initially)</p><p>\u2192 Transition to CEO role as team grows</p><p></p><p><strong>Engineer #1</strong></p><p>\u2022 Ship features 2x faster</p><p>\u2022 Own mobile or desktop platform</p><p>\u2022 Code reviews, architecture decisions</p><p>\u2022 On-call for critical bugs</p><p></p><p><strong>Designer #1</strong></p><p>\u2022 Improve UI/UX based on feedback</p><p>\u2022 Design new features</p><p>\u2022 Marketing website & assets</p><p>\u2022 App Store screenshots</p><p>\u2022 Brand evolution</p><p></p><p><strong>Marketing Lead</strong></p><p>\u2022 SEO & content strategy</p><p>\u2022 Paid acquisition (test & scale)</p><p>\u2022 Email campaigns</p><p>\u2022 Partnership outreach</p><p>\u2022 Community building</p><p></p><p><strong>Customer Success</strong></p><p>\u2022 Answer support tickets (<24h)</p><p>\u2022 Onboarding calls (high-value customers)</p><p>\u2022 Collect feedback & feature requests</p><p>\u2022 Write help docs & tutorials</p><p>\u2022 Monitor churn signals</p>",
      "type": "document",
      "parentId": "team-hiring",
      "childrenIds": [],
      "isCollapsed": false,
      "prefix": "9.2"
    },
    "culture": {
      "id": "culture",
      "name": "Company Culture & Values",
      "content": "<p><strong>Core Values</strong></p><p></p><p><strong>1. User-Centric</strong></p><p>Every decision starts with: \"Does this help the user think better?\"</p><p></p><p><strong>2. Speed & Simplicity</strong></p><p>Fast software, fast decisions, simple solutions</p><p></p><p><strong>3. Privacy First</strong></p><p>Respect user data, local-first by default, transparent practices</p><p></p><p><strong>4. Craftsmanship</strong></p><p>Sweat the details, polish matters, no shipped</p><p></p><p><strong>5. Sustainable Growth</strong></p><p>Profitability > vanity metrics, marathon not sprint</p><p></p><p><strong>Operating Principles</strong></p><p></p><p>\u2022 Ship fast, iterate based on feedback</p><p>\u2022 Default to transparency (build in public)</p><p>\u2022 Async-first communication (respect deep work)</p><p>\u2022 Customer feedback drives roadmap</p><p>\u2022 No jerks, no burnout culture</p><p></p><p><strong>Meeting Culture</strong></p><p>\u2022 No meetings before 10am</p><p>\u2022 All meetings have agenda + outcome</p><p>\u2022 Default to async (Loom, Linear comments)</p><p>\u2022 1-on-1s every 2 weeks (manager \u2194 report)</p><p>\u2022 Weekly team sync (30 min max)</p><p></p><p><strong>Remote Work Policy</strong></p><p>\u2022 Work from anywhere</p><p>\u2022 Overlap hours: 10am-2pm PT (for realtime collab)</p><p>\u2022 Annual offsite (team bonding)</p><p>\u2022 Home office stipend ($500/year)</p><p>\u2022 Co-working allowance if needed</p>",
      "type": "document",
      "parentId": "team-hiring",
      "childrenIds": [],
      "isCollapsed": false,
      "prefix": "9.3"
    },
    "risks": {
      "id": "risks",
      "name": "Risks & Mitigation",
      "content": "<p>Potential failure modes and how to avoid them</p>",
      "type": "chapter",
      "parentId": "root-planning",
      "childrenIds": [
        "risk-market",
        "risk-product",
        "risk-execution",
        "risk-competitive"
      ],
      "isCollapsed": false,
      "prefix": "10"
    },
    "risk-market": {
      "id": "risk-market",
      "name": "Market Risk",
      "content": "<p><strong>Risk: Market too saturated, can't differentiate</strong></p><p></p><p>Reality: Outliner market has 50M+ users, but fragmented. No clear winner like Figma (design) or Slack (communication).</p><p></p><p><strong>Mitigation:</strong></p><p>\u2022 Clear positioning (local-first, fast, privacy)</p><p>\u2022 Niche down initially (writers, researchers)</p><p>\u2022 Obsidian proved sustainable niche SaaS works</p><p></p><p>\u2501\u2501\u2501\u2501\u2501\u2501\u2501\u2501\u2501\u2501\u2501\u2501\u2501\u2501\u2501\u2501\u2501</p><p></p><p><strong>Risk: Market shifts away from outliners</strong></p><p></p><p>Counter: PKM (personal knowledge management) is growing, not shrinking. Remote work = more note-takers.</p><p></p><p><strong>Mitigation:</strong></p><p>\u2022 Stay close to user trends</p><p>\u2022 Pivot to adjacencies if needed (note-taking, wikis)</p><p></p><p>\u2501\u2501\u2501\u2501\u2501\u2501\u2501\u2501\u2501\u2501\u2501\u2501\u2501\u2501\u2501\u2501\u2501</p><p></p><p><strong>Risk: Free tools (Obsidian, Logseq) kill paid market</strong></p><p></p><p>Counter: Obsidian generates revenue (~$10M/year from sync/publish). Users will pay for quality.</p><p></p><p><strong>Mitigation:</strong></p><p>\u2022 Generous free tier (remove friction)</p><p>\u2022 Offer value beyond free tools (sync, mobile, support)</p><p>\u2022 Focus on UX premium (worth paying for)</p>",
      "type": "document",
      "parentId": "risks",
      "childrenIds": [],
      "isCollapsed": false,
      "prefix": "10.1"
    },
    "risk-product": {
      "id": "risk-product",
      "name": "Product Risk",
      "content": "<p><strong>Risk: Users don't convert from free to paid</strong></p><p></p><p>Low conversion (<3%) = not enough revenue</p><p></p><p><strong>Mitigation:</strong></p><p>\u2022 Generous but limited free tier (3 outlines is strategic bottleneck)</p><p>\u2022 Test pricing ($6 vs $8 vs $10)</p><p>\u2022 Add more paid-only features (cloud sync, advanced export)</p><p>\u2022 Improve onboarding (show value faster)</p><p></p><p>\u2501\u2501\u2501\u2501\u2501\u2501\u2501\u2501\u2501\u2501\u2501\u2501\u2501\u2501\u2501\u2501\u2501</p><p></p><p><strong>Risk: High churn (users cancel quickly)</strong></p><p></p><p>If churn >10%/month, LTV collapses</p><p></p><p><strong>Mitigation:</strong></p><p>\u2022 Focus on activation (first outline in first session)</p><p>\u2022 Build habit loops (daily/weekly usage)</p><p>\u2022 Retention features (streaks, stats, templates)</p><p>\u2022 Exit surveys to understand why they leave</p><p>\u2022 Annual plans (locks in for 12 months, lower churn)</p><p></p><p>\u2501\u2501\u2501\u2501\u2501\u2501\u2501\u2501\u2501\u2501\u2501\u2501\u2501\u2501\u2501\u2501\u2501</p><p></p><p><strong>Risk: Product isn't 10x better than alternatives</strong></p><p></p><p>If IdiamPro is only marginally better, hard to switch users</p><p></p><p><strong>Mitigation:</strong></p><p>\u2022 Nail 1-2 killer features (speed? gestures? privacy?)</p><p>\u2022 Make switching easy (import from Notion, WorkFlowy, etc.)</p><p>\u2022 Continually innovate (don't stagnate)</p><p></p><p>\u2501\u2501\u2501\u2501\u2501\u2501\u2501\u2501\u2501\u2501\u2501\u2501\u2501\u2501\u2501\u2501\u2501</p><p></p><p><strong>Risk: Technical debt slows development</strong></p><p></p><p>As product grows, codebase becomes unmaintainable</p><p></p><p><strong>Mitigation:</strong></p><p>\u2022 Allocate 20% time to refactoring</p><p>\u2022 Write tests for critical paths</p><p>\u2022 Hire senior engineers who care about code quality</p><p>\u2022 Periodic architecture reviews</p>",
      "type": "document",
      "parentId": "risks",
      "childrenIds": [],
      "isCollapsed": false,
      "prefix": "10.2"
    },
    "risk-execution": {
      "id": "risk-execution",
      "name": "Execution Risk",
      "content": "<p><strong>Risk: Solo founder burnout</strong></p><p></p><p>Building, marketing, support, everything = unsustainable</p><p></p><p><strong>Mitigation:</strong></p><p>\u2022 Set boundaries (no weekends, 8-hour days)</p><p>\u2022 Outsource non-core (accounting, legal, design)</p><p>\u2022 Hire early if revenue supports it</p><p>\u2022 Consider co-founder (risky but helpful)</p><p></p><p>\u2501\u2501\u2501\u2501\u2501\u2501\u2501\u2501\u2501\u2501\u2501\u2501\u2501\u2501\u2501\u2501\u2501</p><p></p><p><strong>Risk: Can't acquire customers cheaply enough</strong></p><p></p><p>If CAC >$50 and LTV = $120, margins too thin</p><p></p><p><strong>Mitigation:</strong></p><p>\u2022 Focus on organic (content, SEO, word-of-mouth)</p><p>\u2022 Build viral loops (referrals, sharing)</p><p>\u2022 Only do paid ads if CAC <$30</p><p>\u2022 Improve retention \u2192 higher LTV \u2192 more CAC headroom</p><p></p><p>\u2501\u2501\u2501\u2501\u2501\u2501\u2501\u2501\u2501\u2501\u2501\u2501\u2501\u2501\u2501\u2501\u2501</p><p></p><p><strong>Risk: Run out of money before profitability</strong></p><p></p><p>Bootstrap fails if can't reach break-even before savings run out</p><p></p><p><strong>Mitigation:</strong></p><p>\u2022 Keep 12 months runway minimum</p><p>\u2022 Reach profitability in 6 months (conservative goal)</p><p>\u2022 Have backup plan (freelance, part-time job)</p><p>\u2022 Raise angel funding if traction is strong but need more time</p><p></p><p>\u2501\u2501\u2501\u2501\u2501\u2501\u2501\u2501\u2501\u2501\u2501\u2501\u2501\u2501\u2501\u2501\u2501</p><p></p><p><strong>Risk: Hiring wrong people early</strong></p><p></p><p>Bad first hires can kill culture and momentum</p><p></p><p><strong>Mitigation:</strong></p><p>\u2022 Hire slow, fire fast</p><p>\u2022 Start with contractors (test before committing)</p><p>\u2022 Clear role expectations, 90-day review</p><p>\u2022 Culture fit > skill fit (can teach skills)</p>",
      "type": "document",
      "parentId": "risks",
      "childrenIds": [],
      "isCollapsed": false,
      "prefix": "10.3"
    },
    "risk-competitive": {
      "id": "risk-competitive",
      "name": "Competitive Risk",
      "content": "<p><strong>Risk: Notion copies our best features</strong></p><p></p><p>Large player with 30M users could clone IdiamPro</p><p></p><p><strong>Mitigation:</strong></p><p>\u2022 Move fast, stay ahead</p><p>\u2022 Lean into what big cos can't do (local-first, privacy, speed)</p><p>\u2022 Build community (harder to copy)</p><p>\u2022 Vertical focus (Notion is horizontal, we're outliner-first)</p><p></p><p>\u2501\u2501\u2501\u2501\u2501\u2501\u2501\u2501\u2501\u2501\u2501\u2501\u2501\u2501\u2501\u2501\u2501</p><p></p><p><strong>Risk: New competitor launches with VC funding</strong></p><p></p><p>Well-funded startup could outspend us on marketing</p><p></p><p><strong>Mitigation:</strong></p><p>\u2022 Own a niche (privacy-conscious users, local-first advocates)</p><p>\u2022 Superior product (VC funding doesn't = good product)</p><p>\u2022 Community & brand loyalty</p><p>\u2022 Consider raising if needed to compete</p><p></p><p>\u2501\u2501\u2501\u2501\u2501\u2501\u2501\u2501\u2501\u2501\u2501\u2501\u2501\u2501\u2501\u2501\u2501</p><p></p><p><strong>Risk: Obsidian adds structured outlines</strong></p><p></p><p>Closest competitor could negate our differentiator</p><p></p><p><strong>Mitigation:</strong></p><p>\u2022 We have better mobile UX (their weakness)</p><p>\u2022 Obsidian is Markdown-first, we're outline-first</p><p>\u2022 Different user bases (we target less technical)</p><p>\u2022 Partner, don't fight (Obsidian import/export)</p><p></p><p>\u2501\u2501\u2501\u2501\u2501\u2501\u2501\u2501\u2501\u2501\u2501\u2501\u2501\u2501\u2501\u2501\u2501</p><p></p><p><strong>Risk: Apple/Microsoft builds this into OS</strong></p><p></p><p>Platform risk (like Notes app killed some note apps)</p><p></p><p><strong>Mitigation:</strong></p><p>\u2022 Unlikely (outliners too niche for OS-level)</p><p>\u2022 Cross-platform is our moat (Apple can't do Windows/Web well)</p><p>\u2022 Power features beyond what OS would provide</p>",
      "type": "document",
      "parentId": "risks",
      "childrenIds": [],
      "isCollapsed": false,
      "prefix": "10.4"
    },
    "milestones": {
      "id": "milestones",
      "name": "Key Milestones & Timeline",
      "content": "<p>12-month roadmap with measurable goals</p>",
      "type": "chapter",
      "parentId": "root-planning",
      "childrenIds": [
        "milestone-q1",
        "milestone-q2",
        "milestone-q3",
        "milestone-q4"
      ],
      "isCollapsed": false,
      "prefix": "11"
    },
    "milestone-q1": {
      "id": "milestone-q1",
      "name": "Q1 2026: Launch & Validate",
      "content": "<p><strong>Product Milestones:</strong></p><p>\u2705 Fix search functionality (CRITICAL)</p><p>\u2705 Complete platform testing (Web, iOS, Desktop)</p><p>\u2705 Payment integration (Stripe)</p><p>\u2705 User accounts system</p><p>\u2b1c iOS App Store approval</p><p></p><p><strong>Business Milestones:</strong></p><p>\u2b1c Form Delaware C-Corp</p><p>\u2b1c File trademark for IdiamPro</p><p>\u2b1c Complete TOS + Privacy Policy</p><p>\u2b1c Set up business bank account</p><p></p><p><strong>Marketing Milestones:</strong></p><p>\u2b1c Launch marketing website</p><p>\u2b1c ProductHunt launch (Top 5 goal)</p><p>\u2b1c Beta program (20-50 testers)</p><p>\u2b1c First 3 blog posts published</p><p></p><p><strong>Traction Goals:</strong></p><p>\u2022 500 total users by Month 1</p><p>\u2022 2,000 total users by Month 3</p><p>\u2022 100 paying users by Month 3</p><p>\u2022 $800 MRR by end of Q1</p>",
      "type": "document",
      "parentId": "milestones",
      "childrenIds": [],
      "isCollapsed": false,
      "prefix": "11.1"
    },
    "milestone-q2": {
      "id": "milestone-q2",
      "name": "Q2 2026: Growth & Iteration",
      "content": "<p><strong>Product Milestones:</strong></p><p>\u2b1c Cloud backup feature (optional, encrypted)</p><p>\u2b1c Internal node linking [[feature]]</p><p>\u2b1c Breadcrumbs navigation</p><p>\u2b1c Import from Notion, WorkFlowy, Obsidian</p><p>\u2b1c Windows app (Electron)</p><p></p><p><strong>Business Milestones:</strong></p><p>\u2b1c Reach profitability (break-even)</p><p>\u2b1c DECISION: Bootstrap or raise angel round?</p><p>\u2b1c If raising: Pitch 20 angels, close $200-500K</p><p></p><p><strong>Marketing Milestones:</strong></p><p>\u2b1c SEO: 1,000 organic visits/month</p><p>\u2b1c Build email list to 500+</p><p>\u2b1c Launch referral program</p><p>\u2b1c 5-10 customer testimonials</p><p></p><p><strong>Traction Goals:</strong></p><p>\u2022 10,000 total users</p><p>\u2022 500 paying users</p><p>\u2022 $4,000 MRR by end of Q2</p><p>\u2022 <5% monthly churn</p>",
      "type": "document",
      "parentId": "milestones",
      "childrenIds": [],
      "isCollapsed": false,
      "prefix": "11.2"
    },
    "milestone-q3": {
      "id": "milestone-q3",
      "name": "Q3 2026: Scale Features",
      "content": "<p><strong>Product Milestones:</strong></p><p>\u2b1c Node templates (save/reuse subtrees)</p><p>\u2b1c Graph view (connections visualization)</p><p>\u2b1c Publishing: Export outline to web (share link)</p><p>\u2b1c API v1 (read-only)</p><p>\u2b1c Mobile widgets (iOS)</p><p></p><p><strong>Team Milestones:</strong></p><p>\u2b1c Hire Engineer #1 (if revenue supports: $10K+ MRR)</p><p>\u2b1c Hire Designer/Contractor (part-time)</p><p></p><p><strong>Marketing Milestones:</strong></p><p>\u2b1c Launch affiliate program (20% commission)</p><p>\u2b1c Partner with 2-3 productivity influencers</p><p>\u2b1c Publish comparison guides (vs Notion, Obsidian, etc.)</p><p></p><p><strong>Traction Goals:</strong></p><p>\u2022 30,000 total users</p><p>\u2022 1,500 paying users</p><p>\u2022 $12,000 MRR</p><p>\u2022 500+ weekly active outliners</p>",
      "type": "document",
      "parentId": "milestones",
      "childrenIds": [],
      "isCollapsed": false,
      "prefix": "11.3"
    },
    "milestone-q4": {
      "id": "milestone-q4",
      "name": "Q4 2026: Collaboration & Revenue",
      "content": "<p><strong>Product Milestones:</strong></p><p>\u2b1c Collaboration v1 (shared outlines, view-only)</p><p>\u2b1c Real-time sync across devices</p><p>\u2b1c Advanced search (regex, filters)</p><p>\u2b1c Template marketplace (let users sell templates)</p><p></p><p><strong>Business Milestones:</strong></p><p>\u2b1c Reach $100K ARR milestone \ud83c\udf89</p><p>\u2b1c Evaluate Series A (if VC path) or stay bootstrapped</p><p></p><p><strong>Marketing Milestones:</strong></p><p>\u2b1c Launch Team plan (if demand exists)</p><p>\u2b1c Holiday promotion (Black Friday sale)</p><p>\u2b1c Year-in-review content (\"2026 by the numbers\")</p><p></p><p><strong>Traction Goals:</strong></p><p>\u2022 50,000 total users</p><p>\u2022 2,500 paying users</p><p>\u2022 $20,000 MRR ($240K ARR)</p><p>\u2022 Sustainable, profitable business \u2705</p>",
      "type": "document",
      "parentId": "milestones",
      "childrenIds": [],
      "isCollapsed": false,
      "prefix": "11.4"
    }
  },
  "lastModified": 1775243277989
}